import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="ticks")
    g = sns.FacetGrid(data, col="Series")
    g.map(sns.scatterplot, "X", "Y")
    plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.8)
    g.fig.suptitle('What is the correlation between X and Y for each series?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.set_palette("husl")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x="Series", y="X", data=data, ax=ax[0])
    sns.barplot(x="Series", y="Y", data=data, ax=ax[1])
    ax[0].set_title("Mean and Standard Deviation of X for each Series")
    ax[1].set_title("Mean and Standard Deviation of Y for each Series")
    ax[0].set_xlabel("Series")
    ax[1].set_xlabel("Series")
    ax[0].set_ylabel("X")
    ax[1].set_ylabel("Y")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="ticks")
    g = sns.FacetGrid(data, col="Series", hue="Series", col_wrap=2)
    g.map(sns.histplot, "X", kde=False)
    g.map(sns.histplot, "Y", kde=False)
    g.set_axis_labels("X", "Y")
    g.fig.suptitle("What is the distribution of X and Y for each series?")
    plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)
    plt.legend(title="Series")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.lineplot(x='X', y='Y', hue='Series', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y across all series?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="ticks")
    g = sns.catplot(x="Series", y="Y", data=data, kind="box", color="skyblue")
    g.set_axis_labels("Series", "Y")
    plt.title("What is the difference between the four series in terms of X and Y?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
